            "answer_text": "In an atom of any elements, number of protons are equal to the number of electrons. The number of protons is called as the atomic number. Hence an atom contains number of electrons, equal to its atomic number. From the periodic table, Sodium (Na) has atomic number -11. So it has 11 electrons.. ",
